1. Silent cache-miss path violates the review contract. In [corpus_harness.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:521), `CachingEmbedder::load` treats `Ok(None)` as a quiet cold miss, and in [corpus_harness.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:685) `read_cache` returns that same quiet `Ok(None)` whenever either the blob or sidecar is missing. That means first-run misses and partial-cache misses produce no `CORPUS_CACHE_MISS` line, even though this slice’s contract requires every miss to be loud before live embedding proceeds. The validation-on-hit path is otherwise solid (`identity` + `doc_manifest_sha` checked before loading bytes at [corpus_harness.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:692)), but the quiet miss path is still a spec break.

2. The TDD surface does not lock that requirement in. [tests/corpus_harness.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/corpus_harness.rs:18) proves a cold ingest sets `embed_cache_hit == false` and `embedded_live > 0`, but it never captures stderr or asserts the required `CORPUS_CACHE_MISS` emission. As written, the suite would stay green with the silent-miss behavior above.

Everything else I checked looks aligned with the prompt: the cache key includes name/revision/dimension plus subset manifest, hit validation checks identity/manifest before trusting bytes, deterministic write order is explicit, the batched ingest path is still reused verbatim from [corpus_subset.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_subset.rs:370), `query_set` mirrors the EU-7 title-or-lead + SplitMix64 approach, and the Pack-4 test migrations appear behavior-preserving.

